In [[mathematics]], a '''Baer group''' is a [[group (mathematics)|group]] in which every [[cyclic group|cyclic]] [[subgroup]] is [[Subnormal subgroup|subnormal]]. Every Baer group is [[locally nilpotent]].<ref>{{Citation | last1=Robinson | first1=Derek John Scott | title=A course in the theory of groups | publisher=[[Springer-Verlag]] | location=Berlin, New York | isbn=978-0-387-94461-6 | year=1996 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=lqyCjUFY6WAC&pg=PA367 | page = 367}}</ref>

Baer groups are named after [[Reinhold Baer]].

