In mathematics, a '''monothetic group''' is a [[topological group]] with a [[Dense set|dense]] [[cyclic subgroup]]. They were introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Van Dantzig|year=1933}}.  An example is the additive group of [[p-adic integers]], in which the integers are dense.

A monothetic group is necessarily [[Abelian group|abelian]].  

